-- Melbourne Cricket Ground to Host 2015 World Cup Final
-- B y   T r a c y   W i t h e r s
-- 2013-07-30T00:57:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-30/melbourne-cricket-ground-to-host-2015-world-cup-final.html
The 2015 Cricket  World Cup  final
will be played in Melbourne following semifinals in Sydney and
Auckland, the  International Cricket Council  said today.  The opening match will be on Feb. 14, 2015, with the final
scheduled for March 29, the organizers said in an announcement
broadcast live in Australia and New Zealand, the two nations
jointly hosting the event. Fourteen teams will participate in
the 11th version of the World Cup, competing in the one-day, 50-over format.  There are two pools for the event. In Pool A, England joins
Australia, Sri Lanka, New Zealand, Bangladesh and two qualifiers.
Pool B will comprise  South Africa , India, Pakistan, West Indies,
Zimbabwe and two qualifiers, one of which is already confirmed
as Ireland. The top four teams in each group proceed to the
quarterfinals, to be played in Wellington, Sydney, Adelaide and
Melbourne.  New Zealand  and Australia will each host half of the 42
pool games.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tracy Withers in Wellington at 
